340 g Turkey Breast Portions
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
⅓ cup Panko Breadcrumbs
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
½ cup Marinara Sauce
½ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
56 g Baby Spinach
1 tbsp Red Wine Vinegar
1 tbsp Italian Seasoning
½ tbsp Dijon Mustard
1 unit(s) Red Onion
0.13 tsp Pepper*
½ tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Salt*
2.5 tbsp Oil*

Add panko and half the Parmesan to a shallow dish. Stir to combine.
Pat turkey dry with paper towels.If applicable, cut into 2 (4) equal pieces Carefully slice into the centre of each turkey breast, parallel to the cutting board, leaving 1/2-inch intact on the other end. Open up turkey like a book. Season both sides with salt, pepper and half the Italian Seasoning.
Coat each turkey breast all over with mayo.
Working with one turkey breast at a time, press both sides into panko mixture to coat completely.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat.
When hot, add 1 tbsp oil, then turkey. ( NOTE: For 4 ppl, pan-fry turkey in batches, using 1 tbsp oil per batch.)
Pan-fry until golden-brown, 3-4 min per side.
Transfer turkey to a foil-lined baking sheet. Carefully wipe the pan clean.

Spoon marinara sauce over turkey, then sprinkle with remaining Parmesan.
Broil in the middle of the oven until cheese is golden-brown and turkey is cooked through, 4-6 min.**

Meanwhile, c ore, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch slices.
Peel, then cut half the onion into 1/4-inch slices (whole onion for 4 ppl).
Heat the same pan (from step 2) over medium-high.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then onions and remaining Italian Seasoning. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 3-4 min.
Transfer onions to a plate to cool slightly.

Meanwhile, add Dijon, vinegar, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine.

Add spinach, peppers and onions to the bowl with dressing. Toss to combine.
Divide turkey parmigiana and salad between plates.

If you've opted to get turkey breast portions, if applicable, cut into 2 (4) equal pieces on a separate cutting board.Prepare and cook them in the same way the recipe instructs you to prepare and cook the chicken breasts.**